    <text>
        <front>
            <div type="summary">
                <p>
                    Ian Parsons enclosed Penguin Book's draft blurb for The Waves for Leonard Woolf to review and informed him that he could communicate any comments directly to Eunice Frost.
                </p>
            </div>
        </front>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date when="1950-10-20">
                            October 20th, 1950.
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>
                            <persName key="Q703935">Leonard Woolf</persName>, Esq.,
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine>
                            <choice><sic>Monks</sic><corr>Monk's</corr></choice> House,
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine>
                            Rodmell,
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine>
                            Near Lewes, Sussex.
                        </addrLine>
                    </address>
                    <salute>
                        Dear <persName key="Q703935">Leonard</persName>,
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <persName key="Q24845248">Eunice Frost</persName> of 
                    <choice>
                        <orig><orgName key="Q1336200">Penguins</orgName></orig>
                        <reg><orgName key="Q1336200">Penguin Books</orgName></reg>
                    </choice> has just sent <lb/>
                    me the enclosed draft blurb for their edition <lb/>
                    of "<title>The Waves</title>". A copy of their covering <lb/>
                    letter is also enclosed. I have told her <lb/>
                    that I felt sure you would like to see it <lb/>
                    personally, and that I would ask you to <lb/>
                    return it direct to her with any comments <lb/>
                    that you may have.
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        Yours,
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <choice>
                            <abbr><persName key="Q18576354">IMP</persName></abbr>
                            <expan><persName key="Q18576354">Ian Macnaghten Parsons</persName></expan>
                        </choice>/
                        <choice>
                            <abbr><persName key="MAPP0061">HG</persName></abbr>
                            <expan><persName key="MAPP0061">H. Gillian</persName></expan>
                        </choice><note><p>"HG" most likely refers to "H. Gillian", who is documented as the typist. The full name could not be identified.</p></note>.
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
